cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.CO

Reasoning: The paper deals with topics related to graph theory, specifically matchings and edge-coloring in cubic graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CO (Combinatorics). The use of graph theory and combinatorics also suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories.
